1. WannaCry Ransomware Attack (2017) 
WannaCry spread rapidly by exploiting a vulnerability in Microsoft Windows systems. It encrypted files and demanded ransom payments from victims. 
      CIA Triad Impact 
•	Availability (Primary): The attack locked users out of their systems and files, disrupting hospitals, businesses, and government organizations worldwide. 
•	Integrity (Secondary): Encrypted files were altered, making them unusable until recovered. 
•	Confidentiality (Low): The malware focused on encryption rather than stealing sensitive information. 
Most Affected: Availability 
  
     2. Equifax Data Breach (2017) 
Equifax suffered a massive data breach after attackers exploited an unpatched Apache Struts vulnerability. Personal information of approximately 147 million people was exposed. 
      CIA Triad Impact 
•	Confidentiality (Primary): Highly sensitive customer information, including Social Security numbers and financial data, was stolen. 
•	Integrity (Medium): Although data was not significantly modified, unauthorized access reduced confidence in data integrity. 
•	Availability (Low): Business operations continued with minimal service disruption. Most Affected: Confidentiality 
  
     3. NotPetya Cyberattack (2017) 
NotPetya appeared to be ransomware but was actually destructive malware designed to permanently damage systems. It spread through a compromised software update. 
      CIA Triad Impact 
•	Availability (Primary): Organizations lost access to critical systems and operations were severely disrupted. 
•	Integrity (Primary): System files and boot records were permanently destroyed, making recovery impossible without backups. 
• 	Confidentiality (Low): The attack focused on destruction rather than data theft. Most Affected: Availability and Integrity 
  
    4. SolarWinds Supply Chain Attack (2020) 
Attackers inserted malicious code into legitimate SolarWinds software updates, allowing them to gain long-term access to government and enterprise networks. 
     CIA Triad Impact 
•	Confidentiality (Primary): Sensitive government and corporate information was secretly accessed. 
•	Integrity (High): Trusted software updates were modified with malicious code before distribution. 
•	Availability (Low): Systems remained operational because the attack focused on espionage instead of disruption. 
Most Affected: Confidentiality and Integrity 
  
        5. Colonial Pipeline Ransomware Attack (2021) 
The Colonial Pipeline attack was carried out using compromised VPN credentials. The company shut down pipeline operations to contain the ransomware attack. 
        CIA Triad Impact 
•	Availability (Primary): Pipeline services were suspended for several days, causing fuel shortages across the U.S. East Coast. 
•	Confidentiality (High): Attackers stole approximately 100 GB of company data before deploying ransomware. 
•	Integrity (High): Files and systems were encrypted, affecting normal business operations. Most Affected: Availability 
  
