Conclusion 
The five cyberattacks demonstrate that different threats affect different components of the CIA Triad. WannaCry and Colonial Pipeline mainly targeted Availability by disrupting business operations. The Equifax breach primarily compromised Confidentiality by exposing millions of sensitive records. NotPetya severely affected both Integrity and Availability by permanently destroying systems and preventing recovery. SolarWinds compromised Confidentiality and Integrity through a sophisticated supply chain attack that allowed long-term unauthorized access. 
These incidents highlight the importance of implementing strong cybersecurity controls such as timely patch management, multi-factor authentication, network segmentation, continuous monitoring, secure software updates, and regular backups. Protecting all three components of the CIA Triad is essential for maintaining a secure and resilient organization. 
